Team news 

England: Wayne Rooney is set to earn his 100th cap for England against Slovenia at Wembley on Saturday.

The England captain will lead his side out against their closest rivals in Group E. Meanwhile, Andros Townsend and Michael Carrick were both ruled out of the squad through injury.

West Brom forward Saido Berahino could be in line to make his senior international debut, while Stewart Downing could make his first appearance for England since a Euro 2012 warm-up game against Norway in May 2012. 

